# ImportRSoPData function

## Description

The
**ImportRSoPData** function imports a data file containing RSoP data to a WMI namespace. The file must be one generated by a call to the
[ExportRSoPData](https://learn.microsoft.com/previous-versions/windows/desktop/api/gpedit/nf-gpedit-exportrsopdata) function.

## Parameters

### `lpNameSpace` [in]

Pointer to a string specifying the namespace to contain the RSoP data. The namespace must exist prior to calling
**ImportRSoPData**.

### `lpFileName` [in]

Pointer to a string specifying the name of the file that contains the RSoP data.

## Return value

If the function succeeds, the return value is **S_OK**. Otherwise, the function returns one of the COM error codes defined in the Platform SDK header file WinError.h.
